## Configuration Options

```toml
[volume]
curve = "logarithmic"     # linear, logarithmic, exponential, custom
curve_steepness = 9.0     # For log/exp curves (1.0-20.0)

# Custom curve points (only used if curve = "custom")
# Format: [[dial_position, actual_volume], ...]
custom_curve_points = [
    [0, 0],
    [25, 10],     # 25% dial = 10% volume (quiet listening range)
    [50, 35],     # 50% dial = 35% volume (normal listening)
    [75, 65],     # 75% dial = 65% volume (louder)
    [100, 100],
]

[microphone]
curve = "linear"          # Mic often works better linear
```

## CLI Integration

```bash
# Show current curve
surface-dial config get volume.curve
# Output: logarithmic

# Change curve
surface-dial config set volume.curve linear

# Show curve visualization
surface-dial config show-curve
# Output: ASCII visualization of curve
```

