# Description

Integration tests that simulate HID device events for testing without physical hardware, and test cross-module interactions.

## HID Simulation Approach

Since we cannot require physical Surface Dial for CI, use mock HID devices and virtual devices where available.

### Mock HID Device Trait

```rust
// src/hid/mod.rs

use std::time::Duration;

pub trait HidDeviceTrait: Send {
    fn read_timeout(&self, buf: &mut [u8], timeout: Duration) -> Result<usize, HidError>;
    fn write(&self, data: &[u8]) -> Result<usize, HidError>;
    fn get_feature_report(&self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> Result<usize, HidError>;
}

#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum HidError {
    #[error("IO error: {0}")]
    Io(String),
    #[error("Device disconnected")]
    Disconnected,
    #[error("Timeout")]
    Timeout,
}

// Production wrapper
pub struct RealHidDevice {
    device: hidapi::HidDevice,
}

impl HidDeviceTrait for RealHidDevice {
    fn read_timeout(&self, buf: &mut [u8], timeout: Duration) -> Result<usize, HidError> {
        self.device
            .read_timeout(buf, timeout.as_millis() as i32)
            .map_err(|e| HidError::Io(e.to_string()))
    }

    fn write(&self, data: &[u8]) -> Result<usize, HidError> {
        self.device
            .write(data)
            .map_err(|e| HidError::Io(e.to_string()))
    }

    fn get_feature_report(&self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> Result<usize, HidError> {
        self.device
            .get_feature_report(buf)
            .map_err(|e| HidError::Io(e.to_string()))
    }
}
