Current code should work, but may need permission configuration.

### Permission Options

1. **udev rule** (recommended for auto-start):
```bash
# /etc/udev/rules.d/99-surface-dial.rules
SUBSYSTEM=="hidraw", ATTRS{idVendor}=="045e", ATTRS{idProduct}=="091b", MODE="0666", GROUP="plugdev"
```

2. **Add user to plugdev/input group**:
```bash
sudo usermod -aG plugdev $USER
sudo usermod -aG input $USER
```

## Audio Control on Linux

Replace osascript calls with Linux equivalents using:

### PulseAudio (pactl)

```rust
fn get_volume_linux() -> Option<i32> {
    let output = Command::new("pactl")
        .args(["get-sink-volume", "@DEFAULT_SINK@"])
        .output()
        .ok()?;
    // Parse: "Volume: front-left: 65536 / 100% / -0.00 dB, ..."
    let text = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
    // Extract percentage
    text.split('/').nth(1)?.trim().trim_end_matches('%').parse().ok()
}

fn set_volume_linux(vol: i32) {
    let vol = vol.clamp(0, 100);
    Command::new("pactl")
        .args(["set-sink-volume", "@DEFAULT_SINK@", &format!("{}%", vol)])
        .output()
        .ok();
}

fn toggle_mute_linux() {
    Command::new("pactl")
        .args(["set-sink-mute", "@DEFAULT_SINK@", "toggle"])
        .output()
        .ok();
}
```

### PipeWire/WirePlumber (wpctl)

```rust
fn get_volume_pipewire() -> Option<i32> {
    let output = Command::new("wpctl")
        .args(["get-volume", "@DEFAULT_AUDIO_SINK@"])
        .output()
        .ok()?;
    // Parse: "Volume: 0.50" (0-1 scale)
    let text = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
    let vol_str = text.split(':').nth(1)?.trim();
    let vol_float: f32 = vol_str.parse().ok()?;
    Some((vol_float * 100.0) as i32)
}

fn set_volume_pipewire(vol: i32) {
    let vol = vol.clamp(0, 100);
    Command::new("wpctl")
        .args(["set-volume", "@DEFAULT_AUDIO_SINK@", &format!("{}%", vol)])
        .output()
        .ok();
}
```

### Auto-Detection

```rust
fn detect_audio_backend() -> AudioBackend {
    // Check for PipeWire first (modern)
    if Command::new("wpctl").arg("--version").output().is_ok() {
        return AudioBackend::PipeWire;
    }
    // Fall back to PulseAudio
    if Command::new("pactl").arg("--version").output().is_ok() {
        return AudioBackend::PulseAudio;
    }
    // ALSA as last resort
    AudioBackend::Alsa
}
